      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "O'CALDINO (1) is on the quick back-up and drops in weight with Spokes' 2kg claim. Worked hard early from the wide gate and stuck on well to finish third over 1900m at Kilcoy. Conditions suit and proven at the trip. CASTEL TROSINO (7) comes back in grade today and never suited on the Gold Coast Poly with a fading last over 1900m in BM65 class. Proven at the trip and the lugging bit goes on. Sharp improver. OTTOMAN EMPIRE (8) massive form reversal last start when he relished the heavy (10) conditions to score a dominant 4.5 len win over 1420m at Grafton. Open to plenty of improvement and gets the same conditions again. STOICISM (4) proven heavy track mare who can bounce back quickly after finishing sixth over 1900m at the Gold Coast Poly. Can take a hand in the finish with the claim.",
